8.4.20  12:41 pm   What inspired the lyric "when did all the windmills start to turn so slow?" and what does it mean? It really hits different,

     ah, that is precisely the answer

     but I have no concept of why.

      these things are apparently found everywhere in nature, and once you get a taste you get greedy and you never wanna settle for anything less. hitting different and not knowing why is like the gold standard in songwriting. we don't know where these things come from but just know that there are plenty to go around for everyone
